        {
            "name": "Pteranodon",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Pteranodons are quick and agile reptiles with 20-foot wingspans that enable them to hover on wind currents for hours. These creatures have long beaks and equally long crests that protrude from the backs of their heads.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Animal</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"10\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Nature</a></u>)</b>: DC 16",
            "source": {
                "type": "source",
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "Bestiary pg. 272",
                    "alt": "Bestiary pg. 272",
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 272
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Pterosaur",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "On Primeval Wings",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "text": "Although not true dinosaurs,\npterosaurs are often found in\nthe same regions as dinosaurs\nand other megafauna, wheeling\nin the skies above and adding to\nthe general primeval ambiance of\nthese lost worlds.",
                    "source": {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Bestiary pg. 272",
                            "alt": "Bestiary pg. 272",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 272
                    },
                    "subtype": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Pterosaurs are primitive flying creatures. While many are smaller than a human, the two presented below are quite a bit larger. Each of these creatures could pose a serious threat to a person.<br/><br/> These flying reptiles can be found in a wide selection of regions, but they tend to soar above warm or temperate climates.",
            "source": {
                "type": "source",
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "Bestiary pg. 272",
